http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Media-told-to-be-sensible-while-reporting-scandals/article13982059.ece

The media should play a responsible and sensible role while reporting on scandals, Mia Marie Hammerlin, the Linnaeus-Palme faculty fellow from Lund University, Sweden, has said. She was speaking on the topic ‘Media and Political Scandals’ at the Department of Communication and Journalism here on Monday, a press note issued here on Monday said.In the Swedish context, political scandals arising out of the misuse of public money was a serious offence. Politicians would be criticised by the media and they might also face expulsion from their political careers.